<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - DRIVETRAIN FAILURE ANALYSIS - CLUTCH COMPONENTS - RELEASE
        BEARING ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="3">
        <title>RELEASE BEARING ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">A release bearing will fail (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300234">Figure 34</hotlnk>) for one or more of the following reasons:
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300234" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300234" filename="../figg13/G1300234.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Release Bearing Failure</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lack of periodic lubrication (does not apply to sealed bearings).</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Failure to fully release or riding the clutch pedal.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Failure to use the recommended lubricant.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Uneven wear on housing wear pads is caused by worn or damaged cross shaft bushings or cross
                shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300235">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300235" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300235" filename="../figg13/G1300235.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Uneven Wear on Housing Wear Pads</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Excessive housing cover wear can be caused by a linkage system out of adjustment or driver
                shift technique (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300236">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300236" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300236" filename="../figg13/G1300236.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Excessive Housing Cover Wear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
